	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=112959><span id= >Iilolian</span></a><br><span id=notbold>88 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Full instructions...<br><br>Requires...<br>2 Spider Silk<br>MEDIUM Chainmail pattern<br>Emerald<br>2 Large Bricks of Velium<br>2 Coldain Velium Tempers<br>3 Large Bricks of Mithril<br>6 Flasks of Water (not foraged or summoned)<br>3 Celestial Solvent<br>3 Spell research components (Scent of Marr recommended... it's Vendor sold in EC, South Qeynos and Ak'Anon)<br>3 Celestial Solvent<br>3 Jars of Acid<br>3 Blue Diamonds<br>2 Essence of Moonlight (dropped in Kithkor during daylight and Mistmoore during night)<br>1 Swirling Mist (dropped by various Air/Steam Elementals)<br>1 Morning Dew (foraged in Lesser or Greater Faydark)<br>Mortar and Pestle (used by Rogues for Poison Making)<br>Regular Forge<br>Koada'Dal Forge (only in Felwith)<br>Elven Smithing Hammer<br><br>Preparation Steps (can be done in any order)<br>#1 Have a Druid or Cleric of Tunare (29th level or higher) Imbue the Emerald.<br><br>#2 Have an Enchanter (49th level or higher) enchant all 3 Large Bricks of Mithril.<br><br>#3 Combine the 2 Spider Silks (unstacked) in a Tailoring Kit or Loom to produce a Silk Swatch (trivial at Tailoring 15).<br><br>#4 Combine 1 Celestial Solvent and 1 Scent of Marr (see above) in the Pestle and Mortar (no fail combine) 3 times to produce 3 Celestial Essence.<br><br>#5 Combine 1 Blue Diamond and 1 Jar of Acid in a Potters Kiln 3 times to produce 3 Powdered Blue Diamonds (trivial at or below Pottery 93)<br><br>#6 Combine 1 Large Brick of Velium and 1 Coldain Velium Temper in a REGULAR forge (will not work in the Koada'Dal Forge) to produce 2 Velium Rings (stackable)... repeat to produce 2 more, discarding 1 (you only need 3 Velium Rings... this step is trivial at or below Blacksmith 88)<br><br>#7 Combine 2 Essence of Moonlight(unstacked), 1 Morning Dew and 1 Vial of Mist in a Brewers Barrel (trivial at Brewing skill 135) to produce 1 Moonlight Temper.<br><br><br>Intermediate Step #A - Celestial Temper, repeat 3 times<br><br>#1 Take 1 Celestial Essence (from Prep #4, above) and 2 Water Flasks and combine them in a Brewers Barrel to produce 1 Purified Water (trivial at or below Brewing 117)<br><br>#2 Take the Purified Water and 1 Blue Diamond Powder and combine them again in the Barrel to produce Celestial Temper (trivial at Brewing 136)<br><br><br>Intermediate Step #B - Infused Mithril Ring, repeat 3 times<br><br>Take the Elven Smithing Hammer (will be returned, even on a failed combine),1 Celestial Temper, 1 Velium Ring and 1 Enchanted Large Brick of Mithril and combine them in the KOADA'DAL Forge (will not work in Regular Forge) to produce 1 Infused Mithril Ring (trivial at or below Blacksmithing 242)<br><br><br>The Grand Finale<br><br>Take all 3 Infused Mithril Rings (again, unstacked!), the Silk Swatch, the Moonlight Temper, the Medium Chainmail Pattern, the Imbued Emerald and the Elven Smithing Hammer and place them in the Koada'Dal Forge...<br><br>...cross your fingers, click your heels 3 times, shout out &quot;I believe in Fairies!&quot;... pray...<br>and hit 'Combine'... this bit isn't trivial, even at Blacksmithing 250, so don't be too suprised if all you have at the end is your Elven Smithing Hammer sitting on your cursor.<br><br>If you've succeeded, then congratulations!!<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jul 14 13:32:30 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>If they take the ship, they'll rape us to death, eat our flesh and sew our skins into their clothes. And if we're very, very lucky, they'll do it in that order</td></tr>
